  "id": "phekb-febrile-neutropenia-pediatric-labs",
  "source": "phekb",
  "source_id": "febrile-neutropenia-pediatric",
  "name": "Febrile Neutropenia (Pediatric) - Lab Threshold Query (ANC <500)",
  "description": "Tests ability to find pediatric FN patients via the PheKB-published ANC threshold: ANC <500 cells/μL. This is the lab-only path central to the published ELSA-FN algorithm.",
  "prompt": "Find pediatric patients with absolute neutrophil count (ANC) below 500 cells per microliter, indicating severe neutropenia.",
  "prompts": {
    "naive": "Find children with low neutrophils.",
    "broad": "Find pediatric patients with severe neutropenia — absolute neutrophil count (ANC) below 500 cells/μL, the threshold for high-risk febrile neutropenia per the ELSA-FN trial.",
    "expert": "I need to find patients with laboratory-confirmed severe neutropenia, the defining lab criterion of the ELSA-FN febrile neutropenia algorithm. Search Observation resources for the LOINC code representing absolute neutrophil count in blood by automated count, and filter to results below the severe neutropenia threshold — an ANC under five hundred cells per microliter. This lab-only path is central to the published algorithm and will capture cases where neutropenia was detected by laboratory surveillance without a corresponding diagnosis code."
  },
